<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="574" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2206: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-17T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                        1921—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>For Stevens.</p>
                        <p>Your August 6th [<hi rend="italic">16th</hi>] noon. Department approves
                            your attitude. Report immediately by telegraph any further attempts to
                            bring about change of gauge.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>